fat cat help my year old spayed female used to go outside every day and catch mice and play for the past couple of months she has refused to go out and has gained a lot of weight her last vet trip was in january check up was fine and she weighed pounds she is now a solid pounds and i don't know what to do i have cats and i keep food for them available all day she is the only one is markedly overweight but the rest go out every day i tried making her go out some but she hides now what can i do with her we have a foot cat tree to play on indoors and plenty of toys and she plays but she's still getting fatter fatter i had a similar problem with my lb tabby i have three cats total and i had to start feeding them twice a day am and pm instead of free for all they whine a lot in the morning but they all seem to go out more now although they hunt more now too the big guy has stopped getting bigger and our cat food budget is manageable i should mention that i give my cats a mix of diet and hairball food i also noticed that moving into a two story house helped a lot with his weight problem that cat played on the stairs more than any other one and it showed there are also timed feeders you amy want to consider i use one when i go out of town Cat Hamster Garfield Fancy rat Obesity Domestic rabbit Guinea pig Super Size Me Ferret Brown Bear Trapping Housebreaking Taboo food and drink Breastfeeding Sin City Binge eating disorder Atkins Nutritional Approach Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers Pet skunk Dieting Feeder (fetish) Milk The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Tocopherol Fat fetishism Dog Seabird Feral cat Kakapo Ostrich Mountain Gorilla Equine conformation RuneScape quests Anorexia nervosa Kangaroo Chocolate Tiger WNNX (FM) Sea Otter Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Bodybuilding Weight training Andr__s Galarraga Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog Raw food diet Tasmanian Devil Little Britain Socialization Cheese Foie gras Poker jargon Albatross Whaling 2000 Australian